<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870623-0101 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:Seeing the Light</HL><DD> 06/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROP </IN><TEXT>   Greece's Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou, famous for his anti-Americanism and socialist economics, recently told business leaders he wants to attract foreign investment by reducing red tape, deregulating banking and cutting taxes and subsidies. A socialist leader seeing the magic of the market isn't new -- ask Francois Mitterrand or New Zealand's David Lange -- but it's always nice to see a potential convert. </TEXT></DOC>